relation to reason about temporal hyperliveness; i.e., temporal
hyperproperties with an alternation of universal and existential
quantification over the executions of several programs. We provide a Coq
definition of HyCo, a proof of soundness, and several examples
demonstrating how it can be effectively used to prove hyperproperties of
imperative programs with non-determinism and I/O.</p>

},
